      • generateROCpoints

        public java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,java.util.TreeSet<XYPair>> generateROCpoints(java.lang.String mod)
        For a given modality, determines XY coordinates of ROC points for each reader of the study. Moves threshold from minimum to maximum score and calculates false positive fraction and true positive fraction at each sample.
        Parameters:
        mod - Modality for which ROC curves are being determined
        Returns:
        TreeMap where the key identifies a reader and the corresponding value is a set of XY coordinates of ROC points

      • generatePooledROC

        public java.util.TreeSet<XYPair> generatePooledROC(java.lang.String rocMod)
        For a given modality, determines XY coordinates of ROC points for pooled scores of all readers as one group. Moves threshold from minimum to maximum score and calculates false positive fraction and true positive fraction at each sample.
        Parameters:
        rocMod - Modality for which ROC curve is being determined
        Returns:
        Set of XY coordinates of ROC points
